riority"}, {"id": 262252840, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwyNjIyNTI4NDA=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/regression-from-stable-to-stable", "name": "regression-from-stable-to-stable", "color": "e4008a", "default": false, "description": "Performance or correctness regression from one stable version to another."}, {"id": 650731663, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2NTA3MzE2NjM=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-bug", "name": "C-bug", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: This is a bug."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2021-03-27T07:27:42Z", "updated_at": "2021-03-30T14:26:00Z", "closed_at": "2021-03-30T14:26:00Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "### Code\r\n\r\nWhen documenting the handling of whitespace in the [textwrap](https://github.com/mgeisler/textwrap/) crate, I noticed that whitespace is collapsed in inline code. That is,\r\n\r\n```\r\n`\"   foo   \"`\r\n```\r\nis rendered the same as\r\n```\r\n`\" foo \"`\r\n```\r\n\r\nTest it with\r\n```\r\n$ cargo new --lib whitespace && cd whitespace && echo '//! `\"   foo   \"`' > src/lib.rs && cargo doc --open\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Version it worked on\r\n\r\nIt worked on Rust 1.50:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89623/112713538-f08eca00-8ed5-11eb-8a98-675179f60ae2.png)\r\n\r\n### Version with regression\r\n\r\nIt stopped working on Rust 1.51. I tracked down the change to #81558, which removed `white-space: pre-wrap` from the CSS. The page now looks like this:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/89623/112713498-c0dfc200-8ed5-11eb-8c57-efdf26372e74.png)", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bors", "html_url": "https